{
  "texts": [
    "The seamless assimilation of AI technologies into the educational landscape faces numerous impediments, including erratic power supply, deficiencies in knowledge and skills, issues of availability and accessibility, financial constraints, insufficient professional development, resistance to change, and unreliable internet connections, among others.",
    "Actors and stakeholders in the education sector, such as educators, policymakers, curriculum planners, and students, can collaborate to overcome these obstacles [12].In contemporary times, AI algorithms and systems have gained widespread recognition and popularity, particularly within the educational domain.",
    "Tablets have significantly supplanted traditional textbooks in numerous educational institutions, and internet-based learning has experienced a surge in prevalence [65].",
    "The integration of digital tools has revolutionized education and fostered a more active and independent approach to learning.",
    "The advent of new technologies has reshaped communication dynamics, necessitating educators to explore innovative methods to inspire learners and seamlessly adapt to the demands of the new century [61]."
  ]
}